<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Lechon Mehbellzek</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-02 19:39:22</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I would suggest you try talking to the deputy before doing the quest.  If he wont tell you the quest then he wont give you the Skullcap when you turn the items in.  You must raise faction untill he does tell you the full quest.  There are many good quests in town as well as out in Misty thicket.  ONe of the easiest ways to raise faction is to Go out to Misty Thicket and kill goblins from one of the three gobbie camps.  Most drop Runnyeye warbeads.  Turn these into the sheriff on the second floor of the bank next to the Mayor.  You will receive faction and small amounts of money.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps with your questing<BR>
Lechon Mehbellzek<BR>
Guild Cleric Flamma Aeturnus<BR>
Tallon Zek</font></td></tr></table>
