<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Wyldra</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-09-13 15:14:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>I have acquired the 4 skins and am preparing to turn them in. Here's the skinny on where I got them: <BR>
<BR>
Polar Bear skin - Everfrost off of the polar bear cubs, piece of cake to kill these little guys. <BR>
<BR>
Shark skin - Freeport, one swims just off the docks at ship. No problem for a 14th level druid. Other sharks are around too, Lake Rathetear and the Ocean of Tears come to mind. <BR>
<BR>
Grizzly Bear skin - Off Grizzlies in West Karana. Nice blue kill for a 14th level druid. Can also drop off young kodiaks I think. Bears are everywhere (WC, Rathe Mountains...)<BR>
<BR>
Alligator skin - this is the hard one. It is a rare drop off Bull Alligators in the NE corner of Innothule Swamp (vicinity of the tower). My experience was that I took my 24th troll warrior out and slaughtered everything in the area (kind of amusing) including maybe a dozen bulls in two different killing sessions, and I killed everything showing up on the tower too, but no luck. Came back later that day and killed 2 Bulls, got the skin off the second one. <BR>
<BR>
I tried auctioning for the skin previously for quite awhile with no luck at all. And this is on Vallon Zek where there are far more trolls than on other servers. <BR>
<BR>
While this took a little time, it was quite doable. My 14th level halfling druidess had no problem (other than travel time) getting the other skins, and was probably high enough to have killed the bulls as well. Biggest difficulty at L14 in the swamp would be avoiding the other wandering aggros in the area of about the same level (not hard for a druid though). <BR>
<BR>
I look forward to getting the cap and then the "real" cap too, very nice quest with a great reward IMO. <BR>
<BR>
Oh, getting the skin off the bulls with my 24 troll also refutes the notion that the alligator skin won't drop off a character who is too high to gain XP from killing them. <BR>
<BR>
<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
